commit 128dd9e14583895232bdf68ea9c85d7efaee2e99
Author: michelkerkmeester-barter <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 13 08:00:51 2026 +0200

    feat(embeddings,014/012): q8 system default + launcher parity + v3 remediation
    
    System default change: hf-local memory now defaults to q8 dtype (was fp32).
    ~1/4 the RAM (~310MB vs ~620MB) at ~99% quality. Users can opt back to fp32
    via HF_EMBEDDINGS_DTYPE=fp32 in .env.local. All clones inherit the new
    default from source (resolveDtype() fallback in hf-local.ts).
    
    Launcher parity (P0-V3-LAUNCHER-001):
      .codex/config.toml + .claude/mcp.json + .gemini/settings.json now route
      spec_kit_memory through .opencode/bin/spec-kit-memory-launcher.cjs so
      .env.local Setup A overrides actually load on those runtimes.
    
    dtype in EmbeddingProfile + DB filename (P1-V3-005-001):
      Prevents silent fp32/q4/q8 vector mixing in the same sqlite. New DB path
      shape: context-index__hf-local__{model}__{dim}__{dtype}.sqlite.
    
    Voyage egress guard timing (P1-V3-007-001):
      New pre-resolution guard fires when VOYAGE_API_KEY is set with
      EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=auto, BEFORE the auto-resolver picks Voyage.
    
    tcpdump macOS compatibility (P1-V3-007-002):
      Script defaults to -i pktap (Apple's pseudo-interface) with
      TCPDUMP_IFACE env override.
    
    CocoIndex search-only hardening (P1-V3-009-001/002):
      daemon validates project_root is inside HOME before opening DB.
      project_status reads unloaded sqlite directly for accurate counts.
    
    Doc/spec alignment:
      011 completion=100, blocker.md rewritten (no remaining blockers).
      Parent phase map covers 001-012. SETUP_A_RECIPE / 002 / 006 / 009
      no longer reference Qwen3 as baseline.
    
    Out of scope:
      - P0-V3-SEC-001 (GitHub PAT in .env:12) — user manual rotation
      - 027/001 cocoindex complete fork — separate larger track
    
    12 packets + parent strict-validate exit 0.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

