commit e3095ce36a8250caef87e1999d062d466eafe9c2
Author: michelkerkmeester-barter <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed May 13 07:40:04 2026 +0200

    feat(embeddings,014/011): unify cocoindex+memory on EmbeddingGemma; purge Qwen3
    
    Make EmbeddingGemma the Setup A default for BOTH surfaces:
      spec-kit-memory: onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX (fp32, 768d) — ONNX/transformers.js
      cocoindex_code:  google/embeddinggemma-300m (bf16, 768d) — sentence-transformers/Metal
    
    The two model ids point at the same underlying weights, but in different file formats
    (ONNX for Node/transformers.js, safetensors for Python/sentence-transformers). Cocoindex
    on Metal runs much quieter than the prior Qwen3-Embedding-4B (8GB fp16 -> ~600MB bf16).
    
    Source-default changes (so all clones inherit Gemma):
      - shared/embeddings/providers/hf-local.ts: DEFAULT_MODEL -> onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX
      - shared/embeddings/factory.ts: DEFAULT_PROVIDER_MODELS['hf-local'] -> same
      - cocoindex_code/config.py: _DEFAULT_MODEL -> sbert/google/embeddinggemma-300m
      - cocoindex_code/settings.py: default_user_settings -> google/embeddinggemma-300m
    
    Runtime config _NOTE_2 docstrings updated in .codex/config.toml + 4 other configs.
    
    Cocoindex prompt registry (cocoindex_code/shared.py) gets EmbeddingGemma entry with
    "InstructionRetrieval" -> "task: code retrieval | query: " for code-search queries.
    Document-side prompt asymmetry is known suboptimal (~5-10pp recall loss) — cocoindex's
    indexing path doesn't apply doc-prompts; addressing this is a follow-on (likely under
    027/001-cocoindex-complete-fork's scope).
    
    Qwen3 purge:
      - HF cache models--Qwen--Qwen3-Embedding-4B/ deleted (~7.5GB)
      - Source defaults no longer reference Qwen3 anywhere
      - PREFIX_REGISTRY / VALID_PROVIDER_DIMENSIONS / _QUERY_PROMPT_MODELS retain Qwen3
        entries as recognized models for users who opt in, just not the default
    
    014 cascade post-011: 11 packets + parent all strict-validate exit 0.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

