commit 734b9526b40d19514d13dc84ab10d1b129471dff
Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 3 13:36:28 2026 +0200

    chore: consolidate pre-existing working-tree WIP across multiple streams
    
    Single bulk commit of accumulated working-tree changes that were NOT part of the
    spec-130 prompt-knowledge-layering work (already shipped separately). Committed in
    bulk at the owner's explicit request ("commit push to main", "one commit").
    
    Spans ~15 unrelated streams: deep-improvement (skill + test fixtures), specs
    026/028/122/125/126/128/129, system-spec-kit, cli-devin/cli-opencode doc WIP,
    spec-130 sibling metadata + scratch dirs, and .claude/settings.local.json.
    
    Relocates spec 127 (reusable-model-benchmark-framework) into spec 131
    (relocate-model-registry-and-benchmarks): git detected this as ~26 file renames
    (12 at 100% similarity), so content is moved, not lost.
    
    Also drops two ephemeral spec/ADR labels from code comments to satisfy the
    comment-hygiene gate (sk-doc/scripts/validate-doc-model-refs.js,
    system-spec-kit resume-ladder.vitest.ts) and removes a runtime daemon lock file.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

